COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 775, L.D. 1170
1 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 23 by inserting after paragraph A the
2 following:
3 'A-1. The department shall annually send the inventory to the Maine Redevelopment
4 Land Bank Authority and to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
5 jurisdiction over economic development matters.'
6 Amend the bill in section 5 in §4756 in the first indented paragraph in the 6th line (page
7 3, line 2 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "375" the following: ', subchapter 2-A'
8 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 7 and inserting the following:
9 'Sec. 7. 30-A MRSA §5157, sub-§1, ¶E, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 664, §3, is
10 repealed and the following enacted in its place:
11 E. Property that a state, federal, municipal or other governmental entity has determined
12 is surplus or that it does not have the capacity to redevelop; and'
13 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
14 number to read consecutively.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This amendment authorizes the Department of Administrative and Financial Services,
1177 through the Bureau of General Services, to annually inventory all land owned by state
1188 agencies and semiautonomous state agencies. It requires the department to annually send
1199 the inventory to the Maine Redevelopment Land Bank Authority and the joint standing
2200 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over economic development matters. The
2211 amendment also clarifies that the Maine Redevelopment Land Bank Authority may acquire
2222 property that is determined to be surplus by a state, federal, municipal or other
2233 governmental entity.
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2255 (See attached)
